# рҹҸӢпёҸ Hevy Workout Analysis вҖ” Agentic AI Training Coach

An AI-powered training coach that connects to your [Hevy](https://hevyapp.com) workout data and provides evidence-based programming recommendations using a multi-model agent architecture.

## What it does

Ask questions about your training in natural language. The agent pulls your real workout history, analyzes volume and gaps, retrieves sports science literature, accounts for your nutrition/training phase, and returns specific programming recommendations with citations.

**Example queries:**
- *"My incline bench stalled at 200 lbs and I'm cutting at 2500 cal. What should I adjust?"*
- *"Are my arms getting enough volume?"*
- *"What does the research say about training volume during a deficit?"*
- *"What did I do in my last workout?"*

## Architecture

```
User query
    вҶ“
MoM Router (classifies вҶ’ selects model)
    вҶ“
в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
в”Ӯ gpt-4o-  в”Ӯ  gpt-4o  в”Ӯ  direct  в”Ӯ gpt-4o-  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ   mini   в”Ӯ          в”Ӯ  lookup  в”Ӯ   mini   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ(program) в”Ӯ(coaching)в”Ӯ (no LLM) в”Ӯ(research)в”Ӯ
в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ
    вҶ“
Tools: Hevy API вҶ’ Volume Calculator вҶ’ RAG вҶ’ Nutrition Checker
    вҶ“
Anomaly Detection (z-score + Isolation Forest)
    вҶ“
Structured Output (Pydantic)
    вҶ“
Eval Harness (LLM-as-judge, 7/7 passing)
```

### Mixture of Models (MoM)

Instead of routing every query to the same LLM, a lightweight classifier selects the optimal model per query type:

| Query Type | Model | Cost | Example |
|---|---|---|---|
| Lookup | None (direct API) | $0 | "What was my bench PR?" |
| Programming | gpt-4o-mini | ~$0.001 | "What exercises for chest?" |
| Coaching | gpt-4o | ~$0.01 | "My bench stalled during a cut" |
| Research | gpt-4o-mini + RAG | ~$0.001 | "What does the research say?" |

### Anomaly Detection

Three-layer gap detection system:

1. **Rule-based thresholds** вҖ” flags muscles below minimum effective volume (MEV) from sports science literature (Schoenfeld, Israetel)
2. **Z-score per muscle group** вҖ” compares current week against the user's personal rolling baseline, flags deviations > 1.5Пғ
3. **Isolation Forest** вҖ” trains on the full weekly volume profile across all muscle groups to detect abnormal overall training patterns

### Eval Suite

7 test scenarios graded by an LLM-as-judge with specific pass/fail criteria:

- **7/7 passing**, average score **0.89**
- Scenarios include: gap detection, stalled lifts during a cut, deload recommendations, injury modifications, research queries, and data lookups
- Each scenario validates routing accuracy, recommendation quality, safety, and citation of evidence

## Tech Stack

- **LangGraph** вҖ” agent orchestration with conditional routing
- **OpenAI** вҖ” gpt-4o / gpt-4o-mini for generation, text-embedding-3-small for RAG
- **ChromaDB** вҖ” local vector database for sports science literature
- **Pydantic** вҖ” structured outputs for recommendations and analysis
- **scikit-learn** вҖ” Isolation Forest for pattern anomaly detection
- **Hevy API** вҖ” real workout data integration
- **Streamlit** вҖ” dashboard + chat interface
- **pytest** вҖ” eval harness with LLM-as-judge scoring

## Setup

### Prerequisites

- Python 3.12
- [Hevy Pro](https://hevyapp.com) account (for API access)
- OpenAI API key

### Install

```bash
git clone https://github.com/pnair0703/hevy_workout_analysis.git
cd hevy_workout_analysis
python3.12 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install httpx pydantic python-dotenv chromadb openai langgraph langchain-core langchain-openai scikit-learn numpy streamlit pytest
```

### Configure

```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your keys:
#   HEVY_API_KEY=your_hevy_api_key
#   OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key
```

Get your Hevy API key at [hevy.com/settings?developer](https://hevy.com/settings?developer).

### Run

```bash
# Dashboard + chat UI
streamlit run frontend/app.py

# Run the agent directly
python test_agent.py

# Run eval suite
pytest evals/run_evals.py -v -s

# Test individual components
python test_hevy.py       # Hevy API connection
python test_rag.py        # RAG pipeline + nutrition
python test_anomaly.py    # Anomaly detection
```

